text: Talca is a Chilean city with 201.797 inhabitants (2002 census). == History == Talca was founded like Villa San Agustín de Talca by the Spanish José Antonio Manso de Velasco on 1881. == Gallery == File:Talca 1 sur.jpg|The "1 Sur" Street File:Talca Estacion2.jpg|Train Station == References == ==Other websites== *Talca municipality Category:Cities in Chile Category:Capitals of Chilean regions Category:Maule Region
